========== ORIGINAL REQUIREMENTS FOR AN AGENT PLATFORM ==============
Requirements for an Agent Platform:


☐ Instantiation and Session management semantics that allow for fine-grained scoping of Agents (User-Agent like Agents vs. Bots/Service-Agents (Single-Role-based agents))
☐ Need to create and administer feedback loops for agent responses
☐ Cognitive Audit Fabric (Explainability, Traceability of decisions)
☐ Ability to change LLMs; Ability to fine-tune prompts per LLM;
☐ Ability to manage and moderate access to 'Tools'
☐ 
☐ Access to Data - Employed Agent Memory, Enterprise/Organization Memory, Industry/Domain Knowlege, Skills, and Employment Scope; Scope-aware Data Serving applications;
☐ Access to LLMs - Routing, Access Control, A/B Testing, Prompt fine-tuning
☐ Access to Tools - 
☐ Access to External Agents - 
☐ 
☐ 
☐ Observability of the agent applications
☐ Observability of agent usage
☐ Observability of LLM and other resource usage 
☐ Cost Accounting and Control
☐ 
