# Agent By Deployment Nature
## Capable Agents
- Modality Support
- Orchestration Capbilities (Memory, Context, Knowledge)
- Multi-agent patterns/topologies supported
- Interaction Channels and Protocols supported
- LLM expctations (whitelsit/blacklist)

## Skilled Agents
- Tenant, Domain, Function, Role, and Responsibility definitions and expectations as prompts 
- Organization Style, Taste, Guardrails as Prompts 
- Tools Specifications, Knowledge (organization memory) accessible to the agent
- Memory Management, Context Management settings
- Identity; Agent has no credentials to access any other systme unless employed
- Skills can be fine-tuned (more prompts can be layered)
- Skill Spec - Encapsulates all aspects of a Skilled Agent other than the identity, discovery, audit, operability aspects


## Employed Agents
- Scope of work (environment, tools, access tokens)
- Scope and Nature of Authority Delegation (Individual user scope, IAM role scoped, etc.,)
- Identity and Credentials to access other services
- Policies and Restrictions (expressed as prompts)
- Constraints and Preferances of the Delegate (expressed as prompts)
- Employment Spec - Encapuslates all aspects of a Employed Agent other than the identity, discovery, audit, operability aspects


