Governance
Explainability & Observability
Agent Operations - Stop, Blacklist, etc.,




====
Context should handle
	•	Reasoning
	•	Planning
	•	Tool orchestration
	•	Decision making

Capable Agents (Agent Applications that are deployed)
- They have explicit code to handle orchestration with LLM, Tools, and certain other subsystems/modules
- They handle context in a specific way that suites a range of use-cases
- They are ideally domain/industry agnostic but are qualified by the quality of reasoning, orchestration, context management, modalities supported, 



Session is about identity, scoping, and continuity — not reasoning.

Typical session attributes
	•	Session ID
	•	User / actor identity
	•	Start & end timestamps
	•	Channel (web, voice, API)
	•	Conversation transcript
	•	Security / auth context
	•	Conversation-level metadata

A session can live minutes, hours, or days.


Key insight:
	•	Context is assembled
	•	Memory is retrieved or updated
	•	Knowledge is queried
	•	Only chosen outputs are written back to memory

=====


Orchestration Agents will support human-in-the-lopp orchestration using the Hub's semantics to bring agents into the loop

Orchestration Agents support Case Model to integrate into the Hub as a Case Automation System. 

I/O Gateway for MS Teams -> Signals -> Trigger -> (New Case or Action in an existing Case); (New Workflow or Action in an existing Workflow Process)


