Subsystems - Role and Requirements
Personas and their Jobs

Publisher:
- May publish Raw agents or Trained Agent Blueprints as part of their module 
- CI for Raw Agents (Evals)
- CI for Trained Agent Blueprints (sample tenants, environment, resources, etc.,)

SRE
- Deploy and Rollout Raw Agents
- Observe and Operate Raw Agents

Tenant
- Train an Agent
- Publish Trained Agent
- Define a Agent-Oriented System 
- Create a HAT 
- Employ a Trained Agent
- Promote learnings from Employed Agents to Trained Agents
- Manage Employed Agents: tune capacity, constraints, block/unblock; Observe 
- Team Members
- Audit and Supervise Agent Activities 

Hub and Seer Integrations
====
* Workbench as AOS
    - Operation as a collaboration session for the HAT

* Seer Agent Engine as an Automation System for ‘Seer Case’ Automation; [Requires contract between Hub Request to Automation System integration - Signals/Updates]
* Seer Agent Engine as an Employed Agent provider for ‘Rhea Workflow’ Automation; 
* Seer uses Cipher as the Workforce, Customer IAM and all Employed Agents exist in one of the domains and sandboxes of the tenant
* Cipher shall support enrolment of Raw, Trained, and Employed Agents and should also serve as a Agent Registry
* Hub Task Allocation refers to Groups and Agents (Auth Profiles) from the Cipher Sandboxes associated with workbench


# Seer Case Automation:
	- Seer Agent Engine as an Automation System for ‘Seer Case’ Automation; [Requires contract between Hub Request to Automation System integration - Signals/Updates]
	- A Hub Request as a Collaboration Session for the HAT

# Seer Agent as a Hub Application:
	- Seer Agent Engine as an Employed Agent provider for ‘Rhea Workflow’ Automation; 
	- A Hub Request as single Agent's Session
